FBIS4-38716 "drsov106_a_94039" FBIS-SOV-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Japanese Vessels Violate Russia's Sea Border Japanese Vessels Violate Russia's Sea Border LD0106122994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1012 GMT 1 Jun 94 LD0106122994 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Japanese schooners violated Russia's sea borders twice on Tuesday in the section controlled by the 11th post of the South Kuril border detachment. The Russian border troops' press bureau told INTERFAX that five and then another four Japanese schooners had violated the Russian border in the afternoon and evening May 31. All of the schooners were ousted from Russian territorial waters.
